<div id="Idea_2901"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/2901-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2901">Citizenship check for college aid&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/4087-4049">fahimbh</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">8 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">The Department of Homeland Security must check the citizenship papers of college students so that their college (private) can a give them financial aid.<br/>This causes monstrous delays (I work in a university aid office).<br/>I don't know who makes the request for citizenship records, the government or the college, but could the government leave the citizenship check to the colleges and universities? There never was a DHS before 2002, so this check in with the DHS is totally unnecessary. The universities can hire people to check on citizenship records.</div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_2901" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_2901', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2238&topicID=2901')">Comments (2)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_2901"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2238">Records Management</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=college aid citizenship">college aid citizenship</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_2901"></div>
