<div id="Idea_2809"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/2809-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2809">Require agencies to document key activities&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/0-4049">lewisplan</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">9 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Increasingly, government officials evade accountability by refusing to document their activities in written form, whether through memos, emails, fax logs, or whatever.  Supervisors even forbid subordinates from sending them written materials.  There should be a government-wide standard instructing agencies on what to document and preserve for the National Archives. There also should be a government-wide minimum time for preserving documents, whether in paper or electronic format. <br/><br/></div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_2809" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_2809', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2238&topicID=2809')">Comments (0)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_2809"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2238">Records Management</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=records">records</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=documentation">documentation</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=preservation">preservation</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=creation">creation</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=standard">standard</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_2809"></div>
