<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_2603"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/2603-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2603">"Declassify" Cheney's documents&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/3957-4049">lbaskett</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">10 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">As Vice President, Dick Cheney exchanged memoranda that he had stamped "treat as classified."  The Vice President does not have the power to establish his own classification system, so no matter what the stamp says, these documents are NOT classified.<br/><br/>We request that Obama order the appropriate agency to weed out any justifiably classifiable information (sources and methods only) and publish ALL of the rest of Cheney's memoranda online.</div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_2603" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_2603', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2238&topicID=2603')">Comments (1)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_2603"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2238">Records Management</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=vice president">vice president</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=dick cheney">dick cheney</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=classification">classification</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_2603"></div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr id="row_2574">
<td width="120" align="center" valign="top" style="padding-left:10px;">
<div id="DiscussionTopicVote_2574">
<div id="IdeaScale_Vote" align="center"><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_2574', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2238&topicID=2574&vote=1')"><img alt="Vote Up" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_up.gif"/>&nbsp;Looks Promising!</a></div><div style="padding:5px;font-size:2em"><a onmouseout="setTimeout('Bubble.hide()', 500)" onmouseover="Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 10 days ago</div><div>Votes For : 57</div><div>Votes Against : 14</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_2574'))" style="text-decoration:none;" id="TopicVote_2574" href="javascript:Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 10 days ago</div><div>Votes For : 57</div><div>Votes Against : 14</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_2574'))">43</a></div><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_2574', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2238&topicID=2574&vote=-1')"><img alt="Vote Down" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_down.gif"/>&nbsp;I'm Not So Sure...</a></div></div>
</div>
</td>
<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_2574"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/2574-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2574">Avoid Paper-Based Processes&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/0-4049">johnwonderlich</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">10 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Paper-based processes should be digitized.<br/><br/>Electronic reporting systems should be devised for all public filings, and the information should be fed directly into online databases.</div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_2574" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_2574', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2238&topicID=2574')">Comments (2)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_2574"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2238">Records Management</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=digitize">digitize</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=sunlight">sunlight</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=ingestion">ingestion</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=records management">records management</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_2574"></div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr id="row_2563">
<td width="120" align="center" valign="top" style="padding-left:10px;">
<div id="DiscussionTopicVote_2563">
<div id="IdeaScale_Vote" align="center"><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_2563', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2238&topicID=2563&vote=1')"><img alt="Vote Up" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_up.gif"/>&nbsp;Looks Promising!</a></div><div style="padding:5px;font-size:2em"><a onmouseout="setTimeout('Bubble.hide()', 500)" onmouseover="Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 10 days ago</div><div>Votes For : 34</div><div>Votes Against : 6</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_2563'))" style="text-decoration:none;" id="TopicVote_2563" href="javascript:Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 10 days ago</div><div>Votes For : 34</div><div>Votes Against : 6</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_2563'))">28</a></div><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_2563', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2238&topicID=2563&vote=-1')"><img alt="Vote Down" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_down.gif"/>&nbsp;I'm Not So Sure...</a></div></div>
</div>
</td>
<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_2563"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/2563-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2563">Transform Federal Depository Libraries into regional data centers&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/0-4049">solorzanomilton</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">10 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">If we're aiming for full transparency there's going to be a lot of data.  And accompanying will be high-demand for book/document scanning, content management (tagging/annotation, normalizing data), and an overall scope that includes federal agencies scattered across the country.  To help build a quick infrastructure to handle this work why not modernize the existing Federal Depository Library Program?<br/><br/>Establishing depository libraries as the local service center of government accessibility will require infrastructure investment (to update, make efficient library buildings) and technology resources (specialty scanning/printing machines, broadband lines, computers, etc).  But if all 1,250 are turned into local reference points for government data, a few servers and data storage sites will reasonably accommodate a computing cloud architecture.  <br/><br/>Decentralizing data collection and storage throughout the United States will allow for quicker, less burdensome, and hopefully more thorough content generation.  At the very least, local librarians will have a sharper eye for local resources than a DC-based office.  Also, duplicating online storage will hopefully prevent the sort of catastrophic data losses seen when a well-intentioned federal agency simply runs out of storage or accidentally deletes critical documents.</div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_2563" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_2563', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2238&topicID=2563')">Comments (0)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_2563"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2238">Records Management</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=federal depository library program">federal depository library program</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=library">library</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=data centers">data centers</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_2563"></div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr id="row_2536">
<td width="120" align="center" valign="top" style="padding-left:10px;">
<div id="DiscussionTopicVote_2536">
<div id="IdeaScale_Vote" align="center"><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_2536', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2238&topicID=2536&vote=1')"><img alt="Vote Up" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_up.gif"/>&nbsp;Looks Promising!</a></div><div style="padding:5px;font-size:2em"><a onmouseout="setTimeout('Bubble.hide()', 500)" onmouseover="Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 10 days ago</div><div>Votes For : 41</div><div>Votes Against : 7</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_2536'))" style="text-decoration:none;" id="TopicVote_2536" href="javascript:Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 10 days ago</div><div>Votes For : 41</div><div>Votes Against : 7</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_2536'))">34</a></div><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_2536', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2238&topicID=2536&vote=-1')"><img alt="Vote Down" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_down.gif"/>&nbsp;I'm Not So Sure...</a></div></div>
</div>
</td>
<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_2536"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/2536-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2536">Social Security and Medicare Should Treat Recipients With Respect&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/3915-4049">clarkfrazier</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">10 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Social Security and Medicare seem to lack any type of central case hanlding and tracking system.  Many larger corporations support an internal help desk accessible by web, telephone or chat.  Each new incident is tracked and followed proactively until resolved or closed. An existing off the shelf system (best of breed) should be adapted to track all contacts with Social Security and Medicare, especially mailed documents and forms.  Calling Social Security about a problem should not result in someone saying, that there is no information available about matters or documents being processed at a local office.  Every contact and document should be tracked and assigned to a new or open case.  It should not be necessary to use the constituant services of a US Congress member or Senator to resolve routine paperwork stuck somewhere in the cumbersome and disjointed Social Security and Medicare system.  To treat citizens this way is inefficient and disrespectful.</div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_2536" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_2536', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2238&topicID=2536')">Comments (1)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_2536"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2238">Records Management</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=social security medicare respect case management">social security medicare respect case management</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_2536"></div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr id="row_2513">
<td width="120" align="center" valign="top" style="padding-left:10px;">
<div id="DiscussionTopicVote_2513">
<div id="IdeaScale_Vote" align="center"><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_2513', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2238&topicID=2513&vote=1')"><img alt="Vote Up" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_up.gif"/>&nbsp;Looks Promising!</a></div><div style="padding:5px;font-size:2em"><a onmouseout="setTimeout('Bubble.hide()', 500)" onmouseover="Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 10 days ago</div><div>Votes For : 14</div><div>Votes Against : 7</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_2513'))" style="text-decoration:none;" id="TopicVote_2513" href="javascript:Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 10 days ago</div><div>Votes For : 14</div><div>Votes Against : 7</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_2513'))">7</a></div><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_2513', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2238&topicID=2513&vote=-1')"><img alt="Vote Down" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_down.gif"/>&nbsp;I'm Not So Sure...</a></div></div>
</div>
</td>
<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_2513"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/2513-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2513">Make the US Patent & Trademark Office Retain Key records &nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/3906-4049">Patent Examiner</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">10 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">The USPTO has been in the habit of stating that it is not required to retain records on its practices regarding the selection of patent examiners for career development details for more than 2 years.  The USPTO claims that it is supported by OPM regulations in not releasing and choosing to destroy these records that are older than 2 years old.  The USPTO should be made to retain and release as well as post data on the racial and gender profile of its selection practices regarding career development details, hiring practices in Attorneys Offices, etc. because this is an agency that is highly racially stratified.</div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_2513" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_2513', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2238&topicID=2513')">Comments (0)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_2513"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2238">Records Management</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_2513"></div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr id="row_2497">
<td width="120" align="center" valign="top" style="padding-left:10px;">
<div id="DiscussionTopicVote_2497">
<div id="IdeaScale_Vote" align="center"><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_2497', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2238&topicID=2497&vote=1')"><img alt="Vote Up" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_up.gif"/>&nbsp;Looks Promising!</a></div><div style="padding:5px;font-size:2em"><a onmouseout="setTimeout('Bubble.hide()', 500)" onmouseover="Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 10 days ago</div><div>Votes For : 32</div><div>Votes Against : 6</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_2497'))" style="text-decoration:none;" id="TopicVote_2497" href="javascript:Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 10 days ago</div><div>Votes For : 32</div><div>Votes Against : 6</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_2497'))">26</a></div><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_2497', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2238&topicID=2497&vote=-1')"><img alt="Vote Down" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_down.gif"/>&nbsp;I'm Not So Sure...</a></div></div>
</div>
</td>
<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_2497"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/2497-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2497">Have the NTIS (National Technical Information Service) digitize all research reports&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/0-4049">tpn18</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">10 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Have the NTIS (National Technical Information Service) digitize all research reports, and make them available for FREE via the web.  Currently NTIS charges prohibitive amounts for even the smallest reports, even in already-digitized format.  NTIS also offers access to its database through private companies, i.e. paid services.  All of the NTIS-stored reports were already paid for by the taxpayer and should be available electronically at no cost to the public.  This service should NOT be available through a contractor service or any organization that provides "value added", i.e. the reports should be available from an NTIS server without going through any intermediaries which may want payment.</div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_2497" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_2497', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2238&topicID=2497')">Comments (0)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_2497"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2238">Records Management</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=ntis">ntis</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=technical reports">technical reports</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_2497"></div>
</div></td>
</tr>
